# What is Gemini?

Gemini is an Internet protocol for requesting and serving documents (similar in spirit to early web/gopher),
with deliberate constraints to keep it simple, privacy-respecting, and consistent.

## Key ideas (plain language)
* Text-first documents (gemtext)
* Encrypted connections (TLS)
* No scripts, no ads, no tracking mechanisms built into the format
* Simple request/response model

## Vocabulary
* Capsule: a Gemini site
* Client: a Gemini browser/app
* Gemtext: the Gemini text format

